# Staking Flow Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start[User initiates stake] --> Auth{require_auth<br/>staker}

    Auth -->|pass| ValidatePoll{Validate Poll<br/>is Active?}

    ValidatePoll -->|no| Error1["PollNotActive"]
    ValidatePoll -->|yes| ValidateTime{Validate<br/>lock_time}

    ValidateTime -->|current >= lock| Error2["PollLocked"]
    ValidateTime -->|current < lock| ValidateStake{Validate<br/>no existing stake}

    ValidateStake -->|already staked| Error3["AlreadyStaked"]
    ValidateStake -->|not staked| ValidateAmount{Validate<br/>amount}

    ValidateAmount -->|amount <= 0| Error4["StakeAmountZero"]
    ValidateAmount -->|amount < MIN| Error5["StakeBelowMinimum"]
    ValidateAmount -->|valid| ValidateBalance{Validate<br/>balance}

    ValidateBalance -->|insufficient| Error6["InsufficientBalance"]
    ValidateBalance -->|sufficient| Transfer[Transfer tokens<br/>user -> contract]

    Transfer --> UpdatePools[Update yes_pool<br/>or no_pool]
    UpdatePools --> IncrementCount[Increment yes_count<br/>or no_count]
    IncrementCount --> StoreStake[Store Stake record<br/>with timestamp]
    StoreStake --> UpdateStats[Update PlatformStats<br/>total_value_locked]
    UpdateStats --> EmitEvent[Emit StakePlaced<br/>event]
    EmitEvent --> Success[Return Stake<br/>to user]

    Error1:::error
    Error2:::error
    Error3:::error
    Error4:::error
    Error5:::error
    Error6:::error

    classDef error fill:#ff6b6b,color:#fff
```

## Token Flow During Stake

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Token as Token Contract
    participant PM as PredictionMarket

    Note over User: User has approved<br/>token spending

    User->>PM: stake(staker, poll_id, amount, Yes)

    PM->>Token: transfer_from(user, PM, amount)
    Note over Token: Validates:<br/>- Allowance<br/>- Balance<br/>- Amount

    Token-->>PM: success

    PM->>PM: Update yes_pool += amount
    PM->>PM: Update yes_count += 1
    PM->>PM: Store Stake record

    PM-->>User: Stake { amount, side, claimed: false }
```
